Engl. o. Frankr. 33, Tyskl. 37. Vik. adj. i Härnösand 30-31, e. lär. i Växjö 31-33, vik. adj. i Haparanda 34-35, timlär. v. Haparanda småsk:-sem. 35, vik. adj. i Umeå 35-36, Gbgs real 36, e. o. adj. i Östersund 38, adj. i matem. o. fysik v. Eksjö h. a. 1. sed. 44.
translated: Davidsson, Yngve Melker, high school teacher, Eksjö. Born on June 30, 1904 in S. Vi, Kalmar 1., to Melker D. and Hanna Hansson. He passed the matriculation exam in Lund in 1924, received his bachelor's degree in 1930, and completed a probationary year at Gothenburg's higher technical school in 1937. He also traveled to England and France in 1933 and Germany in 1937. He was a substitute teacher in Härnösand from 1930 to 1931, a permanent teacher in Växjö from 1931 to 1933, a substitute teacher in Haparanda from 1934 to 1935, a part-time teacher in Haparanda's primary school from 1935 to 1936, a substitute teacher in Umeå from 1935 to 1936, and a teacher in math and physics at Eksjö's high school starting in 1944.
